headline: PNC Financial Services Fourth-Quarter Results Top Street Views
summary: PNC Financial Services (PNC) reported fourth-quarter results above Wall Street's estimates on Friday

headline: State Street Profit Falls as Expenses Jump
summary: State Street logged lower profit in the fourth quarter, despite achieving what it called record revenue, as expenses jumped.

headline: PNC Profit Rises as Loans Increase

headline: M&T Bank Profit Rises on Higher Net Interest Income
summary: M&T Bank posted higher fourth-quarter profit, boosted by growth in its net interest income and net interest margin.

headline: This Biotech Stock Is Up 100% This Year. Why It’s Soaring Again Today.
summary: ImmunityBio  stock is on a tear in 2026 and it looks like the biotech company’s stellar rally will keep going.  The biotech company said full-year revenue from its bladder cancer drug ANKTIVA was set to surge 700% year-over-year to $113 million, in its preliminary earnings results Thursday.  Earlier this week Immunitybio said the Saudi Food and Drug Authority has approved ANKTIVA for the treatment of patients with non-small cell lung cancer.
